SIMPLE: novelist
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Novelist
<hw>Nov"el*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An innovator; an
asserter of novelty.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Cudworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>nouvelliste</ets>, It.
<ets>novellista</ets>.]</ety> <def>A writer of news.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Tatler (178).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>nouvelliste</ets>.]</ety> <def>A writer
of a novel or novels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Novelize</ent>⟦br⟧
